  <releases>
    <release version="@VERSION@" date="2025-10-03">
      <description>
        <p>Mobile-friendly update with improved adaptive design and bug fixes</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Full mobile and tablet support with 360px minimum width</li>
          <li>Adaptive dialogs with breakpoints for narrow screens</li>
          <li>Game History dialog now uses bottom sheet for filters on mobile</li>
          <li>Game Replay dialog optimized with side panel as bottom sheet</li>
          <li>Speed controls moved to overflow menu on mobile devices</li>
          <li>New Game dialog now properly scrollable on small screens</li>
          <li>Fixed timer expiration crash - game now ends properly when time runs out</li>
          <li>Improved touch-friendly margins and spacing on mobile</li>
          <li>Better adaptive bottom bar with priority-based element hiding</li>
          <li>All dialogs now work seamlessly at mobile screen sizes</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="1.0.0" date="2025-10-02">
      <description>
        <p>First stable release of Draughts - A comprehensive draughts/checkers game</p>
        <ul>
          <li>16 international game variants: American Checkers, International, Russian, Brazilian, Italian, Spanish, Czech, Thai, German, Swedish, Pool, Turkish, Armenian, Gothic, Frisian, and Canadian</li>
          <li>10 AI difficulty levels from Beginner to Grandmaster with intelligent move evaluation</li>
          <li>Three gameplay modes: Human vs Human, Human vs AI, and AI vs AI</li>
          <li>Complete sound effects system with audio feedback for moves, captures, and game events</li>
          <li>PDN (Portable Draughts Notation) export for game analysis and sharing</li>
          <li>Four piece styles: Plastic, Wood, Metal, and Bottle Cap</li>
          <li>Five board themes: Classic, Wood, Green, Blue, and High Contrast</li>
          <li>Full move history with unlimited undo/redo support</li>
          <li>Smooth animations and visual feedback for all game actions</li>
          <li>Keyboard navigation and screen reader accessibility support</li>
          <li>Comprehensive rules documentation for each variant</li>
          <li>Modern GTK4/LibAdwaita interface with adaptive design</li>
          <li>Dark mode support following system theme</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
  </releases>
